<div class="col five-sm clear">
<h2 id="section-top">Staff</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="team-intro">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentc3e94d145cfc49f1913340e61bcb629e">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Origin PAs make a difference" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_SummaryAndPhotoModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=16768"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>At Origin we are a small, hardworking in-house team who are dedicated to managing the day to day provision of our live-in care services through our many PAs. Whilst we all have individual responsibilities you can speak to anyone at Origin should you need advice or to resolve a problem.</p>
<p>The prime function of an Origin PA (sometimes referred to as a Personal Assistant or Personal Care Assistant) is to facilitate a spinally injured person to lead life in the way they want to... to enjoy independence, spontaneity and freedom of choice.</p>
<p>As no two clients are the same so no two PAs are the same either and by definition therefore no two care assignments are the same.  </p>
<p>Origin PAs live with the client for 1-2 weeks at a time helping them with everyday activities such as getting in and out of bed, washing and toileting, shopping and cooking, driving and not forgetting nights out on the town!  Trust, friendship, respect, understanding and compatibility are critical to the relationship between live in carer and client and can be mutually rewarding with many PAs remaining in close contact once they return home or progress their career.</p>
<p>Origin PAs are carefully selected, reference checked and personally interviewed. They are continuously monitored whilst undertaking their duties with ongoing support from a network of Advanced PAs and Care Managers to ensure that the Origin standard is maintained.</p>
<p>All PAs must attend and pass Origin's unique, accredited training in spinal injury care - recognised industry wide to be of the very highest standard. This training equips Origin PAs with the necesarry, specialist skills and the confidence to undertake what can be a challenging role.</p>
<p>Origin PAs work under instruction from their clients within a clearly defined care plan to give clients options for a flexible, independent lifestyle of their choice.</p>
<p>To gain further insight into the role of an Origin PA and read comments from clients about our services please look at our website.</p></div>
</div>
